LAGOS  – The Golden Stars Awards, one of the most rated awards for enter­tainment, sports, and entrepre­neurship, held its second edition last Sunday, 19th of June at the prestigious, Lekki Coliseum. The event kicked off on a beautiful red carpet layout as guests were welcomed to the electrifying re­ception of the event. The Royal Father of the day was HRM. Oba Olusola Adeniyi Olaniyan, Onipokia Of Ipokia Kingdom whose presence was well appreciated by the organ­isers. Present at the award ceremo­ny, which was a mix of entertain­ment, awarding excellence and celebrations were Nollywood stars such as Mr Macaroni, Afeez Owo, Adebayo Tijani, Charles Okocha and a host of others. Speaking on the relevance of the ceremony, one of the or­ganisers, Atinuke Owotutu said; “The event went well and we are entirely grateful to God for the success. The journey wasn’t rosy but somehow we pulled it through with over 1000 guests at the venue. As a team, we con­gratulate the winners and also extend our love to the nominees as well whose work got them the recognition. Moving ahead we are planning a much bigger 3rd edition but in the main time we would keep things low-key.” The award ceremony was sponsored by Mr Johnson Fur­niture, Caesars Luxury Hotel, Oti Jonathan Idowu, Lukan, GxX Foods, RC Cola and a few other brands.